## 10. IMAGE MANIPULATION DOCTRINE (2026-04-01)

### The PNG Padding Problem
Product bottle PNGs have transparent padding baked into the image file.
Setting width:70% or max-height:85% constrains the TOTAL image including padding.
The VISIBLE bottle appears tiny because the padding eats 30-40% of the space.

### The Solution: Absolute + Overshoot
1. Container: relative, overflow-hidden, fixed height or aspect-ratio.
2. Image: position absolute, max-w-none (breaks out of flex constraints).
3. Width/height: 150% (overshoots container, zooms past transparent padding).
4. object-fit: contain (bottle scales proportionally within the 150% space).
5. overflow-hidden on container clips cleanly at card edges.
6. drop-shadow for physical grounding (rgba(0,0,0,0.85), 25px blur).

### Responsive Sizing
- NEVER use inline style for width/height that needs responsive breakpoints.
- Inline styles CANNOT be overridden by Tailwind responsive prefixes (lg:, md:, sm:).
- Use Tailwind classes: w-[150%] h-[150%] lg:w-[135%] lg:h-[135%].
- Only use inline style for properties without Tailwind equivalents (filter: drop-shadow).

### SVG Fallback Pattern
For missing images, render a stroke-based SVG flask at 70% of container.
Activated via img onError handler. Match the same absolute positioning + scale
as the real bottles so grid rhythm stays consistent.

### The Splice Lesson
NEVER splice JSX functions by finding start/end markers and slicing.
Multiple functions may share similar patterns. Off-by-one leaves orphaned brackets.
ALWAYS deploy full file replacements for component rewrites.
If the file is > 200 lines, write it locally, SCP it, verify build.

